  "texts": [
    "Overfitting refers to good performance on training data but decreased performance on test data, harming generalization on small datasets.",
    "Over-smoothing means node features become increasingly similar after multiple graph convolution operations, making it difficult for the model to distinguish different nodes.",
    "To tackle these concerns, researchers have proposed various optimization methods for deep GNNs.",
    "A jumping knowledge (JK) network model was proposed to leverage information from different receptive field sizes, thereby improving the learned representations [39].",
    "Li et al. [40] argued that graph convolutions in GCNs fundamentally amount to a type of Laplacian smoothing, may causing oversmoothing."
  ],
